Unsharp masking typically involves two main steps. First, the
original image is smoothed using a high-pass filter to extract
an edge image, also referred to as a mask. In the second
step, this edge image is added to the blurred version of the
original image to enhance sharpness. Figure 2 illustrates the
flowchart of the proposed methodology, where (−) denotes
the subtraction of the smoothed image from the original to
obtain the edge image, (∗) signifies the application of the
sharpness factor (coefficient bounds) to adjust the enhance-
ment, and (+) represents the addition of the edge image to
the blurred image, resulting in the final sharpened output.
