4.4 Public Datasets and Assessment Metrics
The datasets that are most frequently utilized in the field
include categorical subjective image quality (CSIQ) [41],
Laboratory for Image and Video Engineer (LIVE) [42] and
Tampere Image Database (TID2013) [43]. The CSIQ dataset
consists of 30 reference images and 150 distorted images at
5 different levels of blur with ‘.png’ extension. The LIVE
dataset and the TID2013 dataset each consists of 25 refer-
ence images and 125 distorted images at 5 different levels of
blur with ‘.bmp’ extension. We have also included the Kon-
stanz Artificially Distorted Image quality Database (KADID
10k) [44, 45] which consists of 81 reference images and 405
