When evaluating an image’s sharpness, an algorithm’s
evaluation result is compared against a human’s subjective
judgment to see whether it meets the necessary require-
ments. This is done using the sharpness performance eval-
uation indicators. The sharpness performance evaluation
indicators that are most frequently utilized include the root
mean square error (RMSE), Kendall rank order correlation
coefficient (KROCC), Pearson linear correlation coefficient
(PLCC), and Spearman’s rank ordered correlation coefficient
