In image processing, subjective or visual assessment is the
process of analyzing processed images directly to deter-
mine their efficacy and quality. When human perception is
essential to the image’s structure, this kind of evaluation is
essential to make sure the final visual output satisfies intended
objectives. Visual evaluation is frequently employed in con-
junction with quantitative measurements, particularly in
fields like photography, medical imaging, and remote sensing
where subjective judgment is crucial.
